Breakfast Operator (CBBO)</li>\r\n 	<li>Certified Hospitality Engineering Manager (CHEM)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]','TRAINING & CERTIFICATIONS','','inherit','closed','closed','','121-revision-v1','','','2020-07-28 07:29:11','2020-07-28 07:29:11','',121,'http://188.166.160.223/american/121-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2020-07-28 07:31:27','2020-07-28 07:31:27','[vc_section el_class=\"who-we-are-sec\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595913190130{margin-bottom: 15px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\" el_class=\"welcome-head\"]\r\n<h2><strong>Awards</strong></h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1595913370483{padding-top: 25px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595913306706{margin-bottom: 15px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\" el_class=\"welcome-head\"]\r\n<h3><strong>Julian star</strong></h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"certification-points\"]The Julian Star is the most distinguished service award in the global hospitality industry. The award is issued by the International Hospitality Institute (IHI) in partnership with the American Hospitality Institute (AHI).\r\n\r\nThe Julian Star (also known as the “J Star”) recognizes hospitality establishments and practitioners that are delivering differentiated, and discerning service to their customers. IHI and AHI believe that customer service, at its best, should be intuitive, emotive, and imaginative.\r\n\r\nThe Julian Star is named after Saint Julian, the patron saint of hospitality.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"52\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\"certification-points\"]Winners of the Julian Star will exemplify the spirit of compassion and humility in their dealings with customers, and a servant leadership approach in their interactions with co-workers. Unlike some industry awards which focus on the amenities, luxury level, and location offered by hospitality establishments, the Julian Star rates only the quality of customer service delivered by hospitality establishments and the customer service competency of practitioners.\r\n\r\nSome may compare the Julian Star award with the Michelin Star award for restaurants. The Julian Star is different from the Michelin Star in many respects, although both awards are focused on recognizing excellence. Unlike the Michelin Star, IHI and AHI do not award multiple stars. An establishment or individual is either deserving of the Julian Star or not. There is no such thing as two, three, four, or five Julian stars.\r\n\r\nLess than 1% of applicants will be conferred with a Julian Star. Once an individual earns a Julian Star, the recognition is earned for a lifetime and does not need to be renewed. Establishments that earn the Julian Star will keep the Julian Star designation for 3 years.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text][accordions_pplugins id=\'206\'][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\"certification-points\" css=\".vc_custom_1595920445179{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}\"]\r\n<h3><strong>What Award Winners Receive</strong></h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"certification-points\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>There are no cash prizes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Award winners will receive a certificate and a bronze medallion indicating their achievement at no cost. Award winners will be able to order an optional plaque commemorating their achievement at their own cost.</li>\r\n 	<li>Award winners will be featured on AHI’s and/or IHI’s social media pages.</li>\r\n 	<li>Award winners will be able to add “Julian Star Recipient” to their social media profiles, resumes, and promotional materials</li>\r\n 	<li>Award winners will be announced to the national and international news media and publicized in trade publications and websites.</li>\r\n 	<li>All Julian Star winners will be listed on AHI’s and/or IHI’swebsite permanently. This will allow for verification of establishments and hospitality professionals who have earned the Julian Star.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you or your establishment is interested in being considered for a Julian Star award, and you are based in the United States, contact us by email at <a href=\"mailto:info@americanhospitality.institute\">info@americanhospitality.institute</a> to request additional information on how to apply. If you are based outside the United States, contact us by email at <a href=\"mailto:info@internationalhospitality.institute\">info@internationalhospitality.institute</a>. Application is free. Establishments that express interest in being considered for the Julian Star must agree to waive lodging and dining charges for the IHI or AHI representative who visits the establishment, in the event that an on-site visit is required.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]','AWARDS','','inherit','closed','closed','','191-revision-v1','','','2020-07-28 07:31:27','2020-07-28 07:31:27','',191,'http://188.166.160.223/american/191-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(217,1,'2020-07-28 07:32:50','2020-07-28 07:32:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','217','','','2020-07-29 09:59:54','2020-07-29 09:59:54','',0,'http://188.166.160.223/american/?p=217',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(218,1,'2020-07-28 07:32:50','2020-07-28 07:32:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','218','','','2020-07-29 09:59:54','2020-07-29 09:59:54','',0,'http://188.166.160.223/american/?p=218',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(219,1,'2020-07-28 07:36:12','2020-07-28 07:36:12','[vc_section el_class=\"who-we-are-sec\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595921740400{margin-bottom: 15px !important;}\"]The American Hospitality Institute is the only organization representing all stakeholders in the US hospitality industry including hotels, resorts, restaurants, casinos, spas, bed and breakfasts, peer-to-peer lodging, cruise ships, theme parks, hospitality schools, hospitality students, hotel management companies, REITS, airlines, event planners, transportation companies, entertainment companies, and industry vendors and partners.\r\n\r\nAHI is partnered with its sister organization, the International Hospitality Institute (IHI). True to their charter, AHI and AHI are committed to fostering excellence in the hospitality industry. Toward that goal, IHI and AHI launched the <strong>Julian Star</strong> Award to recognize excellence in the hospitality industry.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Julian Star</strong> is awarded to hospitality establishments and hospitality practitioners who demonstrate exceptional customer service. Less than 1% of nominees will receive the award yearly. Covering all segments of the global hospitality industry, the <strong>Julian Star</strong> is the only award of its kind.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"24\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\" el_class=\"who-we-img\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text]AHI and IHI offer training and certification to hospitality practitioners working at both the property and corporate level. Our mission is to utilize accessible pedagogy to help hospitalitarians acquire requisite competencies.\r\n\r\nAHI and IHI seek to improve working conditions for hospitality practitioners by creating awareness and using advocacy efforts. As a think-thank, our research aim is to influence government and corporate policies.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]','WHO WE ARE','','inherit','closed','closed','','63-revision-v1','','','2020-07-28 07:36:12','2020-07-28 07:36:12','',63,'http://188.166.160.223/american/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(220,1,'2020-07-28 07:42:09','2020-07-28 07:42:09','[vc_section el_class=\"who-we-are-sec\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595912365328{margin-bottom: 15px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\" el_class=\"welcome-head\"]\r\n<h2><strong>Certified Casino Operations Manager (CCOM)</strong></h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\"certification-points\"]The Certified Casino Operations Manager (CCOM) certification is for professionals working in leadership positions in the casino industry who possess the required experience or education.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n<ul class=\"pointed-finger\">\r\n 	<li>2 years of college education or 1 year of relevant work experience</li>\r\n 	<li>A passing score on the CCOM exam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo APPLY, send an email with CCOM in the subject line to <a href=\"mailto:info@americanhospitality.institute\">info@americanhospitality.institute</a>, and attach your resume.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]','Certified Casino Operations Manager (CCOM)','','inherit','closed','closed','','183-revision-v1','','','2020-07-28 07:42:09','2020-07-28 07:42:09','',183,